      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the sponges, 18 to 20 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Line a 12-hole muffin tin with paper cases. Sift the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} into a large bowl. In a jug, whisk together the {{eggs}}, {{whole-milk}}, {{vegetable-oil}}, and {{vanilla-extract}}. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and whisk until smooth. Divide evenly between the cases (about 60 g each). Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 5 minutes, then transfer to a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the buttercream and ice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} until smooth and pale. Sift in the {{icing-sugar}} and {{cocoa-powder}} and beat on low speed to combine, then increase the speed and beat for 3 minutes until fluffy. Add the {{whole-milk}} a tablespoon at a time to reach a pipeable consistency. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a star nozzle and pipe a swirl onto each cooled cupcake, starting at the outside edge and spiralling inward.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
